<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="814" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Korea)/11–845:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-08">November 8,
                                        1945</date>.<lb/>[Received November 14—12:10
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>101. When may we expect directive concerning Korea requested in our
                                22, October 4, and referred to in Department’s 22, October 12 [<hi rend="italic">11?</hi>] We offer our opinion that it is
                                important that action in this matter be taken.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>